HEADWORD: Pression
<hw>Pres"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pressio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pression</ets>. See 4th
<er>Press</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of pressing;
pressure.</def> <rj><au>Sir I. Newton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cartesian Philos.)</fld> <def>An endeavor to
move.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

